\section*{Resources \& Usage Notes}
\textbf{Purpose:} connection and sign‑posting, not therapy.

\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Crisis Support:}
        National or local helplines (e.g., 988 in the U.S.) · Emergency numbers for immediate risk · Text or chat‑based lines.  
  \item \textbf{Professional Help:}
        Licensed counselors, psychologists, psychiatrists · Primary‑care doctors · Community mental‑health centers.  
  \item \textbf{Peer / Community Supports:}
        Support groups, warm lines, faith or cultural organizations with trained lay counselors.  
  \item \textbf{Self‑Help \& Coping Tools:}
        Grounding and breathing exercises · Journaling · Creative outlets · Balanced routines · Mindfulness apps that protect privacy.  
\end{itemize}

\begin{tcolorbox}[highlightbox]
\textbf{Trainer’s Reminders}
\begin{enumerate}
  \item Be transparent about non‑clinical status.  
  \item Validate feelings before offering tools.  
  \item Offer one concrete action only.  
  \item End every conversation with referral language.  
  \item Never diagnose or label conditions.  
\end{enumerate}
\end{tcolorbox}

\accentrule
```

**How it fits**

* The accent bars and consistent type hierarchy mirror the front‑side script pages.  
* The `highlightbox` visually separates the “Trainer’s Reminders,” helping trainees locate key ethical points quickly.  
* Leave at least 1 inch margins so facilitators can jot notes during training.

